quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  17,78,"Establish prayer from the time the sun declines until the darkening of the night, and also [remember] the [Qur'an) recitation at dawn. The dawn recitation is certainly witnessed [by Us]"
  17,79,"Pray during the night, an extra voluntary prayer, as it may well be that your Lord will elevate you to a praiseworthy status"
  17,80,"Say, \"My Lord, Cause me to enter [in all I do] with truth, and cause me to finish with truth, and grant me strength out of Your sustaining grace"
  17,81,"And say, \"The Truth has come, and falsehood has vanished, for, falsehood is bound to vanish"
  17,82,We send down from the Qur'an what is a healing and mercy to the believers. And it only increases the unjust in their loss
  17,83,"for, when We bless a human being, he turns away, and arrogantly distances himself; and when he encounters calamity he despairs"
  17,84,"Say, \"Each one acts in a manner reflecting his own character. Your Lord is fully aware as to who is guided to the best path"